33 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.

379 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
380 
381 
382 template <typename T>
383 class WeakCallbackInfo {
384  public:
385  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
386 
387  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
388  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
389  Callback* callback)
390  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
391  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
392  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
393  }
394  }
395 
396  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
397  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
398  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
399 
400  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
401  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
402  return internal_fields_[0];
403  }
404  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
405  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
406  return internal_fields_[1];
407  }
408 
409  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
410  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
411  return callback_ != nullptr;
412  }
413 
414  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
415  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
416  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
417  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
418  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
419  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
420  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
421 
422  private:
423  Isolate* isolate_;
424  T* parameter_;
425  Callback* callback_;
426  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
427 };
428 
429 
430 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
431 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
432 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
433 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
434 // possible to request a second pass callback.
435 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

646 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
647  public:
651  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
657  template <class S>
658  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
659  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
660  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
661  }
667  template <class S, class M2>
668  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
669  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
670  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
671  }
678  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
679  Copy(that);
680  }
681  template <class S, class M2>
682  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
683  Copy(that);
684  }
685  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
686  Copy(that);
687  return *this;
688  }
689  template <class S, class M2>
690  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
691  Copy(that);
692  return *this;
693  }
699  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
700  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
701  }
702 
703  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
704  template <class S>
705  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
706 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
707  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
708  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
709  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
710 #endif
711  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
712  }
713 
714  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
715  template <class S>
716  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
717  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
718  }

720  private:
721  friend class Isolate;
722  friend class Utils;
723  template<class F> friend class Local;
724  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
725  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
726 
727  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
728  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
729  template<class S, class M2>

777  V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
778  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
779  if (this != &rhs) {
780  this->Reset();
781  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
782  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
783  }
784  return *this;
785  }
789  Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT

6151 struct JitCodeEvent {
6152  enum EventType {
6153  CODE_ADDED,
6154  CODE_MOVED,
6155  CODE_REMOVED,
6156  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6157  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6158  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6159  };
6160  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6161  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6162  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6163  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6164  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6165  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6166 
6167  // Type of event.
6168  EventType type;
6169  // Start of the instructions.
6170  void* code_start;
6171  // Size of the instructions.
6172  size_t code_len;
6173  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6174  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6175  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6176  // code line information which is returned from the
6177  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6178  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6179  void* user_data;
6180 
6181  struct name_t {
6182  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6183  // zero-terminated.
6184  const char* str;
6185  // Number of chars in str.
6186  size_t len;
6187  };
6188 
6189  struct line_info_t {
6190  // PC offset
6191  size_t offset;
6192  // Code postion
6193  size_t pos;
6194  // The position type.
6195  PositionType position_type;
6196  };
6197 
6198  union {
6199  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6200  struct name_t name;
6201 
6202  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6203  struct line_info_t line_info;
6204 
6205  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6206  void* new_code_start;
6207  };
6208 };

6215 enum RAILMode {
6216  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6217  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6218  // Throughput may be throttled.
6219  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6220  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6221  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6222  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6223  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6224  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6225  // in this mode.
6226  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,

6228  // turn off latency optimizations.
6229  PERFORMANCE_LOAD

7808 template <class T>
7809 class Maybe {
7810  public:
7811  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
7812  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
7813 
7814  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7815  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
7816 
7817  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
7818  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
7819  return IsJust();
7820  }
7821 
7822  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7823  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
7824  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
7825  return value_;
7826  }
7827 
7828  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
7829  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
7830  }
7831 
7832  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
7833  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
7834  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
7835  }
7836 
7837  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
7838  return !operator==(other);
7839  }
7840 
7841  private:
7842  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
7843  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
7844 
7845  bool has_value_;
7846  T value_;
7847 
7848  template <class U>
7849  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
7850  template <class U>
7851  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
7852 };
7853

7855 template <class T>
7856 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
7857  return Maybe<T>();
7858 }
7859 
7860 
7861 template <class T>
7862 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
7863  return Maybe<T>(t);

8422  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8423  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8424  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8425  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8426 }
8427 
8428 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8429 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8430  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8431  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8432  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8433  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8434  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8435  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8436  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8437  }
8438  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8439  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8440  }
8441  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8442  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8443  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8444  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8445  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8446  //
8447  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8448  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8449  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8450  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8451  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8452  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8453  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8454  }
8455 };
8456 
8457 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8458 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8459  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8460  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8461  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8462  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8463  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8464  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8465  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8466  }
8467  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8468  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8469  }
8470  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8471  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8472  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8473  }
8474 };

9126 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9127 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9128  typedef internal::Object O;
9129  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9130  typedef internal::Internals I;
9131  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9132  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9133  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9134  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9135  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9136  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9137  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9138  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9139  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9140  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9141  }
9142 #endif
9143  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9144 }
9145 
9146 
9147 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9148 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9149  typedef internal::Object O;
9150  typedef internal::Internals I;
9151  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9152  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9153  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9154  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9155  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9156  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9157  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9158  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9159  }
9160 #endif
9161  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9162 }
